---
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Layout from "../../layout/layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Logger - Docs">
	<Header title="Logger" description="Loxt's main function is to help you log messages with style" />
	<main class="mt-5 gap-5 grid justify-center">
		<p>To start using it create a instance of the Loxt class, and then call its various methods.</p>
		<pre class="bg-zinc-900 px-10 rounded-3xl">
			<code>
<span class="hljs-keyword">import</span> { <span class="hljs-title class_">Loxt</span> } <span class="hljs-keyword">from</span> <span class="hljs-string">&#x27;loxt&#x27;</span>;

<span class="hljs-keyword">const</span> loxt = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> <span class="hljs-title class_">Loxt</span>();

loxt.<span class="hljs-title function_">start</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;Some code...&#x27;</span>);
loxt.<span class="hljs-title function_">ready</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;Initialization code, whatever...&#x27;</span>);
loxt.<span class="hljs-title function_">info</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;Loxt is easy to use!&#x27;</span>);     
loxt.<span class="hljs-title function_">warn</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;You can use colors!&#x27;</span>);      
loxt.<span class="hljs-title function_">error</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;Create your own themes!&#x27;</span>); 
loxt.<span class="hljs-title function_">success</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;You can use themes from other people too!&#x27;</span>);
loxt.<span class="hljs-title function_">start</span>(<span class="hljs-string">&#x27;My Amazing App!&#x27;</span>);
			</code>
		</pre>
	</main>
</Layout>